TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {22227=2013: Served as one of the Bears’ starting pitchers, making 21 appearances and 18 starts…Compiled a 5.72 ERA, the second best on the team, and a 5-13 record over the course of the season…Pitched 96.2 innings, allowing 85 runs and 120 hits…Struck out 41 batters…Recorded one hit in 13 at-bats. 2012: Appeared in 23 games and made 18 pitching starts during her rookie season…Led the team with seven wins and a strikeout to walk ratio of 1.6…Struck out 68 batters in 115.1 innings pitched…Held lefties to a .289 batting average and achieved a 3.62 ERA in conference games. Before Brown: An honor roll student for all four years at South High School…Received the President's Award for Educational Excellence and was a California Scholarship Foundation member…A three-year letter winner as a pitcher for South High School…Served as team captain during her senior year…Was a two-time Most Valuable Player and was named Female Athlete of the Season in 2010…Selected to the Pioneer League first team and the All-South Bay second team, and was also an All-CIF honoree…Three-time Spartan Laurel Award winner…Also a member of the South Bay All-Star Classic Softball team.
